    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "We could provide the `widgetParams`, at least users have access to some information. The use case is more about users that want to cleanup their DOM rather than our own usage. The fact that we rely on a container node is a detail of our implementation. With the `widgetParams` provided to the function users could do:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nconst makeHits = instantsearch.connectors.connectHits(\r\n  function renderHits({ hits, widgetParams }) {\r\n    $(widgetParams.container).html(hits.map(hit => JSON.stringify(hit)));\r\n  },\r\n  function unmount({ widgetParams }) {\r\n    $(widgetParams.container).remove();\r\n  }\r\n);\r\n\r\nsearch.addWidget(\r\n  makeHits({\r\n    container: \".hits\"\r\n  })\r\n);\r\n```",
    "created_at": "2019-07-17T13:45:57Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/2843#issuecomment-512261310",
