    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I don't think it makes even sense to have the unmount function being exposed as another argument of the connector. I believe we should rather see the render function as a side effect in vanilla JavaScript (because manipulating the DOM is a side effect), and then we should clean up the effect in a function _returned_ by the renderer.\r\n\r\nGiven your example above @samouss, that would look like:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nconst makeHits = instantsearch.connectors.connectHits(\r\n  ({ hits, widgetParams }) => {\r\n    $(widgetParams.container).html(hits.map(hit => JSON.stringify(hit)));\r\n\r\n    return () => {\r\n      $(widgetParams.container).remove();\r\n    };\r\n  }\r\n);\r\n\r\nsearch.addWidget(\r\n  makeHits({\r\n    container: '.hits',\r\n  })\r\n);\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt makes even more sense when you start attaching events to avoid memory leaks. This assumes that we get rid of the `init` hook first.\r\n\r\nI've been thinking a lot about our render API lately and I think I've got some interesting ideas that I'll share in multiple RFCs.",
